article:
Origin and meaning The German language name is derived from the profession of
the fisherman. The name Fischer is the fourth most common German surname.

Variants
* Fisher (Anglicized version)
* Fischler
* Vischer
* Fischers
* Fischl
* Fischel
* Fischle
* Fischmann
